  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nAdd `event` or `log` actions to the txlog.  These would track events emitted and include relevant information about them, including their decoding.\r\n\r\nNote that we should include only *one* decoding, namely, the correct one.  We can determine the correct one by the Solidity code that emits the event.  Doing this will require expanding the options to the `decodeEvent` function in codec.\r\n\r\nWe can also add an event log to `data` in the debugger, so that users of the CLI debugger can get a log of events emitted (say, by pressing `e`) without relying on `txlog`.",
